=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Build the heterocycle by cyclizing a 2-chloro-5-formyl-4-ethyl nicotinonitrile derivative with ethylhydrazine to give 4-chloro-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine-5-carbaldehyde | Step 2: Displace the 4-chloro group by SNAr with 4-aminotetrahydropyran to form 3-ethyl-1-ethyl-4-((tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)amino)-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine-5-carbaldehyde | Step 3: Convert the 5-formyl group to 5-aminomethyl by reductive amination with NH3/NH4OAc then NaBH3CN (or H2), giving 5-(aminomethyl)-3-ethyl-1-ethyl-4-((tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)amino)pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine | Step 4: Acylate that aminomethyl group with succinic anhydride to obtain the monoacid intermediate pyrazolopyridinyl-CH2NHCOCH2CH2CO2H | Step 5: Activate the acid (HATU/DIPEA or via acid chloride) and couple with 4-chloro-5-bromobenzylamine to give the target CCc1nc2c(cnn2CC)c(NC2CCOCC2)c1CNC(=O)CCC(=O)NCc1ccc(Cl)c(Br)c1

